## NIH Funding to Canadian Research, 1985–2025

Below is a working dashboard, built end-to-end against a real dataset, as a demonstration of the principles laid out in [mirador](/mirador/). It reads the same data the same way regardless of who opens it; it follows the site's light and dark theme automatically; it tells a focused story rather than presenting a wall of charts.

The dataset is every NIH grant awarded to a Canadian institution between fiscal year 1985 and fiscal year 2025, pulled from [NIH RePORTER](https://reporter.nih.gov/). The headline finding: NIH funding to Canadian biomedical research peaked at $70 million in 2009 and has fallen 44% since.

